
[1]context

   CONTEXT, n. [L. Con and texo, to weave.] The general series or
   composition of a discourse; more particularly, the parts of a discourse
   which precede or follow the sentence quoted; the passages of scripture
   which are near the text, either before it or after it. The sense of a
   passage of scripture is often illustrated by the context.

   CONTEXT, a. Knit or woven together; close; firm.
